    "short_description": {
        "value": "EarthGPT is a pioneering multi-modal large language model (MLLM) designed for universal remote sensing (RS) image comprehension. It unifies multi-sensor and diverse RS interpretation tasks, including scene classification, image captioning, region-level captioning, visual question answering (VQA), visual grounding, and object detection, across optical, SAR, and infrared modalities. It introduces a visual-enhanced perception mechanism, cross-modal mutual comprehension, and unified instruction tuning, and is trained on the large-scale MMRS-1M dataset (over 1M image-text pairs from 34 RS datasets).",
        "confidence": 0.8329
    },
    "paper_link": {
        "value": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2401.16822",
